analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Consolidation persists amid tariff-driven relief. The GMS index at 51 confirms a neutral regime where fiscal-monetary nexus stability hinges on the compression of high-yield credit spreads. While the Supreme Court's intervention against trade tariffs mitigates immediate tail-risk, the flat OGV vector and negative breadth highlight a lack of structural momentum. Liquidity convexity remains stagnant despite marginal gains, necessitating a cautious deployment strategy as regional divergences signal latent volatility within the global macro architecture. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]

reports.ID: Konsolidasi netral pasca-relaksasi tarif. Skor GMS 51 mengonfirmasi rezim netral di mana kompresi spread kredit high-yield menopang stabilitas makro saat ini. Meskipun pembatalan tarif oleh Mahkamah Agung memitigasi tail-risk fiskal, vektor OGV yang datar dan breadth negatif menunjukkan bahwa apresiasi aset belum didukung oleh fundamental yang kuat. Konveksitas likuiditas bersih tetap stagnan sementara divergensi pada indeks Asia memberikan sinyal volatilitas laten, menuntut strategi penempatan yang defensif hingga momentum struktural kembali terakselerasi.
